    "updated_at": "2023-04-25T03:37:17Z",
    "body": "Can reproduce on mac + zsh:\r\n\r\n```zsh\r\nexport STARSHIP_CONFIG=\"~/.config/starship-zsh.toml\"\r\nstarship config character.success_symbol \"[%](white)\"\r\n```\r\n> thread 'main' panicked at 'Error writing starship config: Os { code: 2, kind: NotFound, message: \"No such file or directory\" }', src/configure.rs:245:10\r\n\r\nHowever, without the tilde, it works fine:\r\n```zsh\r\nexport STARSHIP_CONFIG=\"$HOME/.config/starship-zsh.toml\"\r\nstarship config character.success_symbol \"[%](white)\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo the issue is here seems to be related to tilde expansion. I think the code should be changed to support this case?",
